This is a usable proof of concept.

Much of the code and ideas to get this running were taken from the following article.

https://glyph.twistedmatrix.com/2020/08/nice-animations-with-twisted-and-pygame.html

There's a link to the code in the article itself.

Q: How do I use this?

A: One person runs the server and the other runs the client. The ports need to match. I think the settings.py need to match too.

Q: Ports and IP match, why doesn't it work?

A: You might need to do something with port forwarding.
